history.content:
We're working on a variety of ways to make the online 16A lab experience fun and educational, and we expect it will prepare students for future lab classes.

The workload of the summer class will be fairly high (20-30 hrs/week) since the course moves twice as fast compared to the semester version, so we don't recommend taking this class at the same time as another summer course.
Unfortunately, we're unable to offer EECS 47D over the summer.

I am thinking of taking EECS 16A over the summer. Will the online class prepare me for the labs in 16B? What would the workload for the class be like? And is it possible to take EECS 47D over the summer instead since I have taken Math 54 already?
